<span id="freeTextContainer7347472816519975418">If you can categorize this novella as Gothic Horror then I have my own interpretation of it&apos;s ambiguous story.<br/>In my opinion Madam Counsuelo dwelled into a devilish cult due to her loss of husband and his infertility. She lived long and defeated death. Eventually she conjured up a younger herself in shape of Aura. As far as goes for Felipe Montero. He was always there to come along. That ad was always there for him. He&apos;s incarnation of Her dead husband.<br/>Unique thing about this novel is that it&apos;s n</span>
  <span id="freeText7347472816519975418" style="display:none">If you can categorize this novella as Gothic Horror then I have my own interpretation of it's ambiguous story.<br />In my opinion Madam Counsuelo dwelled into a devilish cult due to her loss of husband and his infertility. She lived long and defeated death. Eventually she conjured up a younger herself in shape of Aura. As far as goes for Felipe Montero. He was always there to come along. That ad was always there for him. He's incarnation of Her dead husband.<br />Unique thing about this novel is that it's narration is completely carried out in second person.<br />Certainly a book which should be read again. A far better novrllete than my rating.</span>
