<div id="review_3811248994" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3811248994" />
    <a title="Czarny Pies" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/29160274-czarny-pies"><img alt="Czarny Pies" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1400687408p2/29160274.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3811248994?book_show_action=true">Feb 01, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Czarny Pies" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Czarny Pies" href="/user/show/29160274-czarny-pies">Czarny Pies</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780374511715" href="/book/show/595395.Aura">review of another edition</a>

          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">Gringo teenagers learning Spanish.</span></div>

          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Czarny by: </span>
      A young fan of Buffy the Teenage Vampire Slayer.
  </div>


          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29160274-czarny-pies?shelf=spanish-lit">spanish-lit</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3811248994" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15864694277309271248">Four stars for the bilingual edition. <br/><br/>It is entirely appropriate that Salem the cat from Sabrina the Teenage Witch appear on the cover of this stellar work aimed at North American teenagers who are taking Spanish in high school. The subject is likely to please the young readers especially those who were recently fans of Twilight and other teen vampire novels.<br/><br/>Fuentes&apos; clear prose will be manageable for young Anglo-Saxons who are beginning to learn Spanish. The translation by Lysander Kemp is a de</span>
  <span id="freeText15864694277309271248" style="display:none">Four stars for the bilingual edition. <br /><br />It is entirely appropriate that Salem the cat from Sabrina the Teenage Witch appear on the cover of this stellar work aimed at North American teenagers who are taking Spanish in high school. The subject is likely to please the young readers especially those who were recently fans of Twilight and other teen vampire novels.<br /><br />Fuentes' clear prose will be manageable for young Anglo-Saxons who are beginning to learn Spanish. The translation by Lysander Kemp is a delight to read. <br /><br />The blurb on the dust-jacket asserts that the style of "Aura" is similar to that found in the Gothic tales of Poe and Isaak Dinesen. I concur and would add Henry James to the list as I can see traces of the "The Aspern Papers" and "The Turn of the Screw" in Fuentes' novel. Ultimately the argument can be made that "Aura" is true literature and prepares the young student for more texts such as "Cien años de soledad" by Marquez or "Pedro Páramo" by Rulfo in that the subject matter is how the dead of previous generations take over the lives of following generations.<br /><br />I am not entirely convinced. This is teenage vampire novel whose modest merits work only in the classroom. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="15864694277309271248" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


